# ✍️ Typography Rules

## Purpose
Ensure typography is consistent across all components, pages, and breakpoints.

---

## Fonts
- **Display/Headings** → `Behind The Nineties`, sans-serif
- **Titles/Body** → `Overused Grotesk`, sans-serif

---

## Token Usage
1. **Semantic tokens only**
   - ✅ `--font-size-title-xs`
   - ❌ `font-size: 20px;`

2. **Responsive scaling**
   - Mobile → Tablet → Desktop defined in `Responsive-*.json`.
   - Always use responsive typography tokens (`title-xs-mobile`, etc.).

3. **Line height**
   - Must come from semantic line-height tokens.
   - ❌ `line-height: 32px;`
   - ✅ `line-height: var(--line-height-body-md);`

4. **Weight**
   - Only use defined semantic weights: Regular, Medium, Semibold, Bold.
   - No custom numeric weights outside token definitions.

---

## Accessibility
1. Minimum font size = 16px body text on mobile.
2. Titles and headings must preserve hierarchy:
   - `h1` → `heading-h1`
   - `h2` → `heading-h2`
   - `h3` → `heading-h3`
   - etc.
3. Line height must always be ≥1.4 for body text.
4. Contrast ratio must meet WCAG 2.1 AA.

---

## Example
```css
h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-overused-grotesk);
  font-size: var(--font-size-title-lg-mobile);
  line-height: var(--line-height-title-lg-mobile);
  font-weight: 600;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-title-lg-tablet);
    line-height: var(--line-height-title-lg-tablet);
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-title-lg-desktop);
    line-height: var(--line-height-title-lg-desktop);
  }
}
